				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I investigated the DMC wait-state behavior more by generating a tone manually and adjusting the loop delay until it synchronized with a square wave. This agrees with previous measurements of 4 clocks per DMC byte read. But when I increase the loop delay by one clock, it stays in sync. I'm guessing that in some cases, only 3 wait-states are inserted, somehow related to the instruction being executed. I tried tepples' suggestion of using various instructions (including BRK) but that didn't seem to affect it. I don't even know exactly when the DMC read is occuring each loop iteration, making it more difficult to determine what's happening.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

